body.p: Isomerization in stomach reduces fraction absorbed, i.e., only a fraction of pravastatin in the stomach reaches the intestinal lumen: (1-F_iso_pra). Isomerisation of pravastatin to isopravastatin and trihydroxypravastatin in the stomach.
F_iso_pra of dose is isomerized, (1-F_iso_pra) reaches intestine.

parameter.name: Km for pravastatin export via MRP2

body.p: Fraction absorbed, i.e., only a fraction of the pravastatin in the intestinal lumen is absorbed. This parameter determines how much of the pravastatin is excreted in every round of the enterohepatic circulation.

Also, this parameter is dependent on OATP2B1 function, taking into consideration there may be SNPs hindering/enhancing the enzyme's function in the active process of the uptake of pravastatin. If OATP2B1 function is hindered, there would be more pravastatin excreted into faeces than absorbed and vice versa. (added: 16.03.2022)
F_pra_abs of dose is absorbed. (1-F_pra_abs) is excreted in feces.

log(2) ~ 0.693 used for conversion of half-life injection time to injection rate.
Import of pravastatin via OATP1B1 (SLCO1B1) from the plasma in the liver. Here the genetic variants of SLCO1B1 have their effects.

body.p: Export of pravastatin via MRP2 from the liver in the bile. Here the genetic variants of MRP2 have their effects.
Irreversible export of pravastatin via Michaelis-Menten-Kinetics
Transport of pravastatin via bile to the intestinal lumen. This is the enterohepatic circulation of pravastatin.
Irreversible transport of pravastatin via Mass-Action-Kinetics
Import via OATP2B1 is irreversible at apical membrane of enterocytes.
